#: ../../E/elegant.rst:5
msgid "elegant"
msgstr "elegant"

#: ../../E/elegant.rst:7
msgid "adj\\."
msgstr "形容詞"

#: ../../E/elegant.rst:9
msgid ""
"[common; from mathematical usage] Combining simplicity, power, and a certain"
" ineffable grace of design. Higher praise than ‘clever’, ‘winning’, or even "
":ref:`cuspy`\\."
msgstr ""
"[一般的。数学の用法より] "
"単純さと力強さ、そして設計における言い表しがたいある種の優雅さを兼ね備えていること。‘clever’や‘winning’、あるいは\\ "
":ref:`cuspy`\\ よりもさらに高い賛辞。"

#: ../../E/elegant.rst:12
msgid ""
"The French aviator, adventurer, and author Antoine de Saint-Exupéry, "
"probably best known for his classic children's book *The Little Prince*\\, "
"was also an aircraft designer. He gave us perhaps the best definition of "
"engineering elegance when he said \"A designer knows he has achieved "
"perfection not when there is nothing left to add, but when there is nothing "
"left to take away.\""
msgstr ""
"フランスの飛行家・冒険家・作家であり、おそらく古典的な児童書\\ *The Little Prince*\\ で最もよく知られているAntoine de"
" Saint-"
"Exupéryは、航空機の設計者でもあった。彼は「設計者は、もう付け加えるものが何もなくなったときではなく、もう取り去るものが何もなくなったときに、完璧に到達したことを知る」と述べ、おそらく工学的優雅さの最良の定義を我々に与えてくれた。"
